# Svelte & SvelteKit

## Stack
- Svelte 5, SvelteKit, TypeScript; optional: Supabase, Drizzle.

## Code Style and Structure
- Follow naming conventions; use TypeScript for type safety; use Svelte runes (`$state`, `$derived`, etc.) for reactivity.
- Use Shadcn color conventions when using Shadcn; follow SvelteKit project structure (routes, layouts, +page.server, +layout).

## Component Development
- Keep components focused; use runes for local state; use classes for complex state (e.g. state machines) with `$state` in the class.
- Use `+page.svelte` and `+page.server.ts` for routes; use `+layout.svelte` for shared layout.

## State Management
- Prefer runes for component state; use classes when state is complex (e.g. `class Counter { count = $state(0); increment() { ... } }`).
- Use load functions and form actions for server data; use stores only when shared across components.
